node.text:
.
asked me in a comment if I had a timeline of my fitness journey and I didn’t. So I took the time to do one for all you who follow me and support me. 

Now I try to be as transparent as possible when it comes down to my fitness. This week alone I’ve been getting so many backlash about how I didn’t lose this naturally and how it was impossible. So many disgusting comments and people writing to me in my DM saying that I’m a FRAUD”! I don’t know what makes people think that I am or have them the idea.

Yes I was wearing disposable garments that appear to be the ones people wear when under going surgeries, I had no idea. I went to get a sauna session. Some people said that I wasn’t truthful with my results, nobody here knows me like that personally besides my family and close friends. Y’all decided to follow me because you see some REAL RESULTS! I never faked anything. I’m a real genuine person with a great heart and care for people. 

I tried my best to make this video for those who are losing hope and are struggling forreal.  Get DMs about people who are not mentally in the right state of mind, depressed.

You may not know but I was depressed when I started. I was down I was sad I didn’t love myself, I wanted to eliminate myself from this world. I tried, but my God my Lord and Savior gave me strength and I prayed every day to Him crying to help me. 

I didn’t feel good about myself at all I was the biggest one in my family. Nobody in my family is fat or big. It doesn’t even run in our family. When I gained weight I was in a very tough spot. I was in a relationship that was mentally & emotionally abusive. I was drinking my life away I became an alcoholic and drank my feelings away and the pain I ensured. 

I would go to stores to try things in in H&M and they didn’t fit. I had holes in my pants cause my thighs rubbed together. I was disgusted with myself cause I’d how let myself go so carelessly. Then to hear people say here that I had SURGERY is sooo freaking misleading and absurd.

My story is long, so long I could write a book about it. (One day)

This video represents me! 

I hope I gave you some hope ❤️

node.text:
👉 Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best mindset, nutrition and fitness tips 
 
👉  Follow @bodysmartfitness 
 
The team at @bodysmartfitness want you to know the truth about diets, nutrition, food, fitness and the mindset hacks that will ensure your success. 
 
😀 We all want to feel good. 
 
😀 We all want to feel happy. 
 
⭐️ We all want to be a success (however success looks for us). 
 
@Bodysmartfitness blend a powerful trilogy of mindset, nutrition and fitness education to help people stop being stuck in a yo-yo cycle of fads and frustration. 
 
🌎 Founded by Jaymie Moran and with a global team of online coaches in the UK, America and Australia, the team coach women to get sustainable results for life without giving up the foods they love. 
 
💬 Jaymie said, "We wanted to start the Body Smart Fitness YouTube channel to give even more people the right science-backed information, inspiration and tools to create lasting results. Basically, we want to give you the TRUTH." 
 
💬 "Nothing gets me more annoyed and frustrated than people remaining stuck in a trap of yo-yo diets and ineffective exercise for years, coupled with a mindset that has been shaped by you thinking you're a failure every time you try and fail a diet. You're not a failure, you have been lied to." 
 
😥 "The diet industry keeps you trapped. My team and I are here to help you break free from that trap." 
 
💪 "Because losing weight is the easy part." 
 
🤯 "It is keeping it off that is hard." 
 
👉 Access @bodysmartfitness YouTube channel via the link in bio. Don't forget to subscribe and click the notification bell so you get first access to the videos. 
 
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness 
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness 
 Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness 
 
#nutrition #weightloss #cleaneating #abs #exercise #muscle #instafit #protein #healthyfood #gymlife #fat2fit #healthychoices #cardio #weightlosstransformation

node.text:
.
.
To get rid of fat deposits on your back, you’ll need to start by creating a caloric deficit. That means that you’ll need to burn more calories during the day than you consume.

In addition to cutting calories, you’ll get rid of back fat more quickly if you focus your exercise routine to target the muscles in your upper and lower back.

Adding high-intensity interval exercise (HIIT) to your routine, along with working out these specific muscles, will start to give you the results that you’re looking for. 
.
.
By @fitonomyapp

#quarentreino em casa tbm da pra chorar 😅💪🏽 ·

1- Agachamento peso corporal 
Realizar 3x series dessa sequência c/ 30seg descanso por série 
30rep completas +
30rep curtas +
30seg isometria 
2- 3x series dessa sequência - 30 seg descanso por série 
Afundo +Agachamento+ Isometria- A cada passada para cada lado (total de 10 para cada perna) realiza 5 agachamentos em movimento acelerado , no final , 1 min de isometria ( costas na parede)

3- Agachamento Búlgaro ( pés apoiado na cadeira/ banco/ sofá ) 4x15rep cada lado sem descanso 
4- Elevação de quadril unilateral ( tronco apoiado na cadeira/banco/ sofá) 4x20rep cada lado sem descanso 
5 - 4 apoios ( realizar os movimentos cadência lenta ) 3xseries para cada lado - 10seg de descanso ao final de cada série 
15 rep - joelhos em extensão .+
15rep - joelhos flexionados 
6- Panturrilhas ( utilizar um degrau ou apoio)
5x30seg de execução ( total amplitude ) - 15 seg descanso
.
.
.

node.text:
Full Leg Day Killer 🔥💪
.

Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.
Credit @graoficial #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

The Fat Loss Formula is actually pretty simple (despite what marketing companies will lead you to believe)
Follow👉 @coach.stuartfmunnich

Eat in a caloric deficit, get high protein, lift heavy 3-5 days per week in the gym, and do HIIT on a few off days. 

That's it. It's not complicated and it works like crazy.
-
You don't need to detox or cleanse, you don't need to drink apple cider vinegar, and you don't need to do long boring cardio or even to stop eating the foods you love.
💪
🦵
And, just so you know, I’m putting together a brand-new programme starting Monday 13 September. 

This is specifically for successful busy women, who struggle with lack of time to take care of their body, who want to get back in shape, losing 20 lbs while improving their energy level in the next 90 days without giving up the foods you love or doing unsustainable restrictive fad diets.

It’s a remote programme, so you can join from anywhere in the world.🏝🏕🏠

node.text:
Six circuit exercises each for 45 seconds each, repeated four times! 😁

When traveling, or taking vacation - it’s okay that you’re not in you’re revisit routine of things! I promise you, you won’t lose your progress that easily. Stay active when away from home. This can include walking, exercise, and many more depending on your location. Come back home with a jump start back into your routine. It’s also not the end of the world if you took complete rest off either 🙏🏻

Give this go & enjoy! ✨

cc: @dreathomas

node.text:
HOW TO BURN BELLY FAT HOUR-BY-HOUR,

Dear reader,

My name is Emma, I’m 29 years old and I would like to tell you something personal about myself.

One day last September I just broke down and started to cry.

I reached my breaking point, I felt like I was going to have a nervous breakdown.

I was living an unhealthy lifestyle. I was unhappy, always tired, and I lacked self-confidence!

I happened one Monday morning right after I got on the bathroom scale to weigh myself.

I had been on a strict diet for nearly 3 months.

Now the scales said I weighed 175 pounds. I just couldn’t believe it!

I’d only lost 2 pounds in 3 months!

Maybe this doesn’t sound like a big deal to you, but to me it felt like a tragedy.

I had been trying to lose my belly fat for the last 3 years, I had tried everything.

The results were always the same…

But I don’t want you to feel sorry for me, there’s no need for that.

Because my story has a very happy ending!

I found an amazing way to lose belly fat that I never dreamed existed!

Without using weird pills or anything like that!

I discovered Alice Delgado’s home workout plan, and it changed my entire life.

It’s called The 30 Day Challenge and the amazing thing is the speed at which this plan works!

It is rather remarkable to throw off as much as 3 pounds of fat the very first weekend!

All while following easy instructions, which will lead you to the best version of yourself!

This home workout plan has been a Godsend to me.

I got a sparkling new body in less than 30 days!

I now have a flat stomach, I have more energy and I always feel happy! My friends say I look younger!

It boosted my self-confidence!

Will this workout plan work for you? It is actually 100% guaranteed!

Click the link in @ultrabodyfit bio to access this amazing workout plan now!

You will also see different body transformations (the 2nd is mindblowing!!)

👇🏽Get instant access now!

👉 Factors that influence body weight:

Social media consumption  
Cultural valuation of food  
Smoking  
Exposure to food advertising  
Energy density  
Alcohol intake  
Speed of eating  
Portion size  
Cost  
Employment  
Pressure to cater to different tastes  
Childhood activity  
Childhood habits  
Parent obesity  
Trauma  
Lack of education  
Occupational activity  
Transport use  
Unemployment  
Cost of physical exercise  
Safety of walking  
Access to physical exercise/recreational activity facilities  
Hormone regulation 
Sleep deprivation  
  
💯 However... the #1 factor that always determines body weight is   
  
ENERGY BALANCE! ⚡️  
  
Your calories in, vs your calories out.  
  
⬆️ The factors above can influence your calorie intake and your calorie output.  
  
The reason for your current body weight is your calorie consumption vs your calorie output.  
 
☝️ It sometimes feels easier to blame other factors, this is why the team are so passionate about people understanding energy balance and the role it plays on body composition.  
  
❌@bodysmartfitness are never there to judge, just because calories in vs calories out is the science, doesn't make it easy to adhere to.  
 
👯‍♀️ Their 1:1 educational coaching with clients help learn about the factors that affect their health and teach them the science behind fat loss so they sustain their results long term.

🔥 GLUTES 🔥

Strong glutes are important for proper pelvic alignment, propulsion during running, and even single limb stance support. Strong glutes also help to support the lower back during lifting motions, and prevent knee injuries during lifting and running exercises. So keep them Glutes STRONG !

Here are some exercises, you can easily do at home: 👇

✅ Lying Glute Kicks 3x10
✅ Donkey Kicks 3x12
✅ Plie Squat 3x14
